# 01. Get the list of the network interfaces of the machine without displaying and detail
#     for these interfaces. Only the list of names.(BLUE)

ifconfig -l

# man ifconfig: configure network interface parameters. 
# It is used to assign an address to a network interface and/or
# configure network interface parameters.
# The -l flag may be used to list all available interfaces on the system,
# with no other additional information. 
# -l is mutually exclusive with all other flags and commands,
# except for -d and -u. 
